1
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:12,696
(Previously) The view is beautiful.
It would be even better with a lover.

2
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:15,080
And… do you have one?

3
00:00:15,440 --> 00:00:19,960
Just broke up with her. I proposed to her.
And she said she would work in Vietnam.

4
00:00:20,080 --> 00:00:21,120
So, she denied me.

5
00:00:21,160 --> 00:00:23,960
- When will you stop picking on me?
- Your banana cake is trash!

6
00:00:24,120 --> 00:00:25,080
That's it!

7
00:00:25,120 --> 00:00:27,559
Did you see him?!
He was trying to screw with me!

8
00:00:27,560 --> 00:00:28,320
Nava, stop!

9
00:00:28,480 --> 00:00:31,920
Ever thought? If you weren't like this,
you might've already been his boyfriend.

10
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:34,120
But I don't know how
he feels about me.

11
00:00:34,280 --> 00:00:36,320
What made you decide
to seek treatment with me?

12
00:00:36,360 --> 00:00:38,480
I want to get cured from this condition.

13
00:00:38,520 --> 00:00:40,000
He doesn't seem ready at all.

14
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:42,900
"Love Like a Bike" (Episode 4)

15
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:03,999
(How are you doing?)

16
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,640
(You can tell me anything.)

17
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:33,639
(How are you doing?)

18
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:36,160
(You can tell me anything.)

19
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:09,839
(I'm sorry, P'Doc, )

20
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:12,480
(but I don't want to do this anymore.)

21
00:04:27,440 --> 00:04:29,600
Thank you. See you next time.

22
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:35,879
(Come to my shop, or I'll cut your pay.)

23
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:37,920
What the hell is wrong with him?

24
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:20,680
You're wasted.

25
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:26,160
What do you want?

26
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,840
Nothing.

27
00:05:28,880 --> 00:05:30,720
Can't I just want you to be here?

28
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:35,360
Just spit it out. I've got work to do.

29
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:45,840
Drink with me first.

30
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:47,720
Or else…

31
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:49,840
I'm cutting your pay.

32
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:53,760
What the hell is your problem?

33
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:57,080
I just want someone to drink with.

34
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:00,760
Go ahead and cut my pay.

35
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:02,480
I'm not drinking.

36
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:06,560
You…

37
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:11,440
You want a piece of me? Hmm?

38
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:14,280
Do whatever you want.

39
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,640
I just wanted someone to drink with.

40
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:16,480
Can't you stay and drink with me?

41
00:07:56,880 --> 00:07:59,160
Oh, Auntie Phailin. Tawan, wake up.

42
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:01,400
It's okay. No need to wake him.

43
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:03,280
Let him sleep.

44
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:14,440
I just came to check if he was here.

45
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:18,760
He didn't pick up my calls,
and he didn't call back either.

46
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:23,960
He probably had his phone on silent.

47
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:27,040
But he's been here with me.

48
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:28,640
Not going anywhere.

49
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:30,440
I see.

50
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:32,720
You two are quite something.

51
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:35,680
The other day
you almost wrecked the kitchen.

52
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:38,080
When did you two become so close?

53
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:44,840
But it's good. Stay on good terms.

54
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,960
Now, get me a drink, dear.

55
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,760
On the rocks.

56
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:53,600
Coming right up, Ma'am.

57
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:10,040
Here you go.

58
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:11,200
Thank you.

59
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:27,120
Tawan might act tough on the outside,
not as gentle as his siblings.

60
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:32,200
But he's actually a very kind person.

61
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:36,999
If he ever does anything

62
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:38,480
to hurt your feelings,

63
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:40,600
please don't take it to heart.

64
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:43,720
Sometimes, he just doesn't know

65
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:46,360
how to show kindness to others.

66
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:51,000
I won't.

67
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:53,800
I don't mind it at all.

68
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:56,120
Thank you.

69
00:09:56,880 --> 00:09:59,880
Please take care of Tawan.

70
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:06,520
Yes.

71
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:08,960
I'll take care of him, Auntie.

72
00:10:11,840 --> 00:10:13,040
Thank you.

73
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,800
Come, lie down properly.

74
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:47,520
I went to therapy...

75
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:54,520
but it's not working.

76
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:58,440
Treatment doesn't work in just one go.

77
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:00,200
It takes time.

78
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,960
We're all rooting for you, man.

79
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:05,400
Come on, you can do this.

80
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:13,520
Look, there's your P'Doc.

81
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:19,160
P'Doc! Over here!

82
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:21,440
James, hold this for me.

83
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:22,480
What?

84
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:27,880
Sailom!

85
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:29,560
Where are you going?!

86
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:38,960
Please look after this for me.

87
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:50,760
Are you thinking what I'm thinking?

88
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:52,840
Something's up with those two.

89
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:55,760
It's so obvious.
You could see it from Pluto.

90
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:00,240
Now we have four bikes.

91
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:01,600
How can we practice cycling?

92
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:04,480
We wait.

93
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:14,720
Sailom, what's wrong?

94
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:20,040
Nothing!

95
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:23,200
Even if something was wrong,

96
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:25,160
why would you even care?!

97
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:29,800
Sailom, calm down and listen to me.

98
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:35,640
Can you tell me what happened?

99
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:39,960
Why did you decide to stop the treatment?

100
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:46,480
Whether I continue...

101
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:48,800
or not,

102
00:13:49,520 --> 00:13:52,360
it's my business. Stay out of it.

103
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:57,000
But you told me before...

104
00:13:58,280 --> 00:13:59,880
that you wanted to get better.

105
00:14:03,640 --> 00:14:06,240
Are you afraid the treatment won't work?

106
00:14:07,120 --> 00:14:09,240
If that's the case,

107
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:11,000
please trust me.

108
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:14,120
Once we start,

109
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:17,600
you will definitely recover.

110
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:20,680
Look at it like it was riding a bike.

111
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:23,480
If you have a clear destination,

112
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:26,680
you might face some
obstacles along the way.

113
00:14:26,960 --> 00:14:30,840
But if you don't stop
riding and keep going,

114
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:34,400
you'll reach the finish line one day.

115
00:14:39,560 --> 00:14:43,200
You have to be brave enough
to leave the past behind.

116
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:47,480
P'Doc...

117
00:14:49,520 --> 00:14:51,880
I agreed to the treatment because

118
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:56,920
I thought you could make me better.

119
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:03,000
But you refused to treat me yourself.

120
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:07,480
If this treatment is like

121
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:10,240
riding a bike, just like you said.

122
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:14,320
Now,

123
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:18,960
you've cycled
far away and left me behind.

124
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:51,240
Doc.

125
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:54,000
P'Doc.

126
00:15:54,480 --> 00:15:55,480
Hey.

127
00:15:55,880 --> 00:15:57,320
Hey, Doctor!

128
00:15:57,960 --> 00:16:00,120
- Yeah?
- Why are you spacing out?

129
00:16:03,240 --> 00:16:05,040
Yeah, what's up with you?

130
00:16:13,120 --> 00:16:14,960
I don't even know where to start.

131
00:16:17,040 --> 00:16:18,960
You're acting weird.

132
00:16:22,160 --> 00:16:24,400
Sailom wants me to be his doctor.

133
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:29,400
Then what's the problem?

134
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:30,720
Just treat him.

135
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:34,680
If only it were that simple.

136
00:16:36,920 --> 00:16:38,520
It's just...

137
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:44,840
He thought of me
more than just doctor and patient.

138
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,400
What did you do?

139
00:16:52,160 --> 00:16:54,760
I transferred his case
to another doctor.

140
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:57,080
I can't do it.

141
00:16:57,920 --> 00:16:59,600
It's medical ethics.

142
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:02,920
But now he's furious

143
00:17:04,320 --> 00:17:05,960
and refusing all treatment.

144
00:17:09,160 --> 00:17:11,000
I'm at my wits' end.

145
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:13,680
Listen, Doc.

146
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:16,280
If he refuses treatment,

147
00:17:16,320 --> 00:17:18,280
that's on him. It's his life.

148
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:21,960
But I want him to get better.

149
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:26,160
Because if he doesn't recover,
I don't see how he'll survive out there.

150
00:17:27,760 --> 00:17:29,560
I don't want to see him suffer anymore.

151
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:51,120
Guys, listen.

152
00:17:52,480 --> 00:17:57,840
When I said I wanted to quit
being a host, I meant it. I'm done.

153
00:17:58,360 --> 00:18:01,360
Why? You've earned a lot from that.

154
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:05,760
Yeah.

155
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:07,560
Nah,

156
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:10,079
I feel like I found something

157
00:18:10,080 --> 00:18:13,160
more important than money.

158
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:16,960
You dating someone?

159
00:18:19,473 --> 00:18:21,553
I can't really say that I'm dating him yet.

160
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:26,280
I just want to prove to him

161
00:18:26,760 --> 00:18:28,960
that he's the only one for me.

162
00:18:30,720 --> 00:18:32,000
Damn...

163
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:34,520
I wanna see the face of the guy

164
00:18:34,560 --> 00:18:37,200
who tamed the legendary Sky.

165
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:39,999
I met him at the club.

166
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:43,560
He's a client nothing like the others.

167
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:46,280
Get it? It's like...

168
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:49,560
- A client?
- Yeah.

169
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:53,040
Are you sure you want to date a client?

170
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:59,280
I don't know if it's a good idea or not.

171
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:05,480
All I know is...

172
00:19:07,120 --> 00:19:08,400
I like him.

173
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:20,760
Thanks, man.

174
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:23,440
Wait a sec...

175
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:26,240
One loves his patient.

176
00:19:26,320 --> 00:19:27,880
The other falls for a client.

177
00:19:28,560 --> 00:19:29,800
And you say thanks?

178
00:19:30,840 --> 00:19:32,080
What the heck?

179
00:19:33,560 --> 00:19:35,600
It's simple, Tawan.

180
00:19:35,640 --> 00:19:37,520
If you love someone,

181
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:41,160
you must let them know.

182
00:19:41,480 --> 00:19:43,480
Don't leave them guessing

183
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:47,360
how they feel about you
or you feel about them.

184
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:51,760
Otherwise, that love
might turn into hate.

185
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:56,920
Hey! Are you lagging?

186
00:19:56,960 --> 00:19:58,000
Why?

187
00:19:58,360 --> 00:19:59,920
Got someone on your mind?

188
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:05,240
Tell us.

189
00:20:06,360 --> 00:20:07,360
I do.

190
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,480
But I'm not into “talking.”

191
00:20:11,040 --> 00:20:13,600
- I'm into “doing it.”
- Whoa, damn!

192
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:14,816
Which is your favourite position?

193
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:16,880
That's wicked.

194
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:29,760
It's them, Tawan!

195
00:20:30,840 --> 00:20:31,840
Get'em!

196
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:40,160
Ouch!

197
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:42,080
Hold still, will you?

198
00:20:42,120 --> 00:20:43,760
Then be more gentle, will you?

199
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:52,280
Man… you shouldn't have messed
with his girlfriend. You almost got killed.

200
00:20:52,520 --> 00:20:55,120
How was I supposed to know?!

201
00:20:55,200 --> 00:20:57,440
She said they were already over!

202
00:20:57,760 --> 00:21:00,360
Gosh, you shouldn't have done that.

203
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:02,000
So what?

204
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:04,240
Stop moving. Let me fix your wound.

205
00:21:08,760 --> 00:21:10,000
That stings!

206
00:21:10,440 --> 00:21:12,639
Dammit! I wouldn't have helped you!

207
00:21:12,640 --> 00:21:15,320
And who asked for your help?
I didn't ask for it!

208
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:18,720
Look at yourself!
And you're still cocky!

209
00:21:18,760 --> 00:21:19,760
So what?!

210
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:21,360
Both of you, stop arguing!

211
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:23,200
Fine, fine!

212
00:21:23,320 --> 00:21:25,080
But don't you dare tell Mom!

213
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:26,760
I don't want another lecture!

214
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:29,640
Deal. If we tell,

215
00:21:29,880 --> 00:21:31,320
we're all dead anyway.

216
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:35,320
Whoever breaks it does
the dishes for a whole month!

217
00:21:35,560 --> 00:21:38,240
Promise.

218
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:51,280
Cheers!

219
00:22:05,120 --> 00:22:07,633
(Thanyawarin Hospital)

220
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:50,800
I'm thinking about quitting the host job.

221
00:22:56,240 --> 00:22:57,240
Why?

222
00:22:58,520 --> 00:23:00,600
I just... don't want to do it anymore.

223
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:10,520
How are your wounds? Still hurting?

224
00:23:11,560 --> 00:23:12,800
A little.

225
00:23:16,800 --> 00:23:18,440
Have you eaten yet?

226
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:21,200
Not yet.

227
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:24,920
Want to grab some food?

228
00:23:26,760 --> 00:23:28,280
Aren't you still mad at me?

229
00:23:28,720 --> 00:23:30,960
I am, but I'm hungry.

230
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,880
Thank you.
Here, the rice vermicelli.

231
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:46,400
- What did you order for yourself?
- Instant noodles.

232
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:58,319
No seasoning needed, I think.

233
00:23:58,320 --> 00:24:00,400
None. This place is legit.

234
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:02,000
I must try.

235
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:04,720
Hmm. This is great.

236
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:17,920
I never thought of eating a meal
with you without alcohol.

237
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:20,720
It's nice.

238
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:22,600
What nice?

239
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:26,400
Just…

240
00:24:27,840 --> 00:24:29,520
eating in peace,

241
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:33,880
no loud music,

242
00:24:35,120 --> 00:24:36,800
no one bothering us,

243
00:24:37,840 --> 00:24:42,080
and I don't have to
keep entertaining anyone.

244
00:24:43,560 --> 00:24:45,520
I usually eat alone.

245
00:24:46,160 --> 00:24:48,959
But... having you here as a friend

246
00:24:48,960 --> 00:24:50,320
isn't bad either.

247
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:53,280
Wait... friend?

248
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:54,920
So we're friends now?

249
00:24:54,960 --> 00:24:56,640
Yeah, of course.

250
00:25:01,560 --> 00:25:02,720
Say “Ah.”

251
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:04,720
Eat this.

252
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:06,960
Feeding you as a friend.

253
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:08,640
Friend?

254
00:25:13,760 --> 00:25:16,360
If you weren't my friend,
I wouldn't share my meatballs with you.

255
00:25:19,640 --> 00:25:21,320
Then have this.

256
00:25:23,240 --> 00:25:24,240
Liver.

257
00:25:24,680 --> 00:25:26,840
If you weren't my friend,
you wouldn't get this either.

258
00:25:30,080 --> 00:25:31,080
Like it?

259
00:25:31,320 --> 00:25:33,440
Love it. How did you know I like liver?

260
00:25:33,480 --> 00:25:34,520
You like it, huh?

261
00:25:34,760 --> 00:25:36,160
And it's sweet.

262
00:25:37,800 --> 00:25:39,080
And Nava,

263
00:25:39,520 --> 00:25:41,720
let's go on the bike trip this Saturday.

264
00:25:42,560 --> 00:25:44,120
Sure, I'm in.

265
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:47,040
It'll be much more fun if you're there.

266
00:26:35,800 --> 00:26:37,120
What are you doing here?

267
00:26:38,120 --> 00:26:39,160
Why?

268
00:26:40,200 --> 00:26:42,440
Can't I come and watch you sing?

269
00:26:45,760 --> 00:26:46,880
You can.

270
00:26:57,120 --> 00:27:00,440
I'm heading back after this can.
Need to check on my grandma.

271
00:27:00,880 --> 00:27:02,200
She's not well.

272
00:27:03,720 --> 00:27:04,880
Mm-hmm.

273
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:12,239
If you love someone,

274
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:15,320
you must let them know.

275
00:27:15,480 --> 00:27:17,159
Don't leave them guessing

276
00:27:17,160 --> 00:27:20,999
how they feel about you
or you feel about them.

277
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:24,200
Otherwise, that love
might turn into hate.

278
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:26,680
Dindin,

279
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:31,720
are you coming on the bike trip with me?

280
00:27:33,400 --> 00:27:34,840
I have to go anyway.

281
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:36,720
I'm your employee.

282
00:27:37,680 --> 00:27:40,120
No... I mean, yeah, I know that.

283
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:42,400
What I meant was...

284
00:27:44,273 --> 00:27:46,433
do you want to go biking with me?

285
00:27:48,080 --> 00:27:49,880
Like riding right by my side.

286
00:27:56,360 --> 00:27:58,400
If you want me by your side,

287
00:27:59,480 --> 00:28:00,920
then I'll go.

288
00:29:14,440 --> 00:29:15,920
If this treatment

289
00:29:16,520 --> 00:29:19,240
is like riding a bike,
just like you said.

290
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,000
Now,

291
00:29:23,400 --> 00:29:26,120
you've cycled far away
and left me behind.

292
00:29:56,720 --> 00:29:57,960
Sailom!

293
00:30:02,320 --> 00:30:03,400
Wait!

294
00:30:04,200 --> 00:30:05,520
I'm sorry!

295
00:30:37,040 --> 00:30:38,120
Sailom,

296
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:43,000
I know I let you down.

297
00:30:44,392 --> 00:30:46,800
I failed you by not being your doctor.

298
00:30:47,440 --> 00:30:49,280
But know this…

299
00:30:50,680 --> 00:30:53,320
I never had any intention
of leaving you behind.

300
00:30:54,840 --> 00:30:57,560
The reason I'm here today
is to apologize.

301
00:30:58,320 --> 00:31:00,520
Even if I can't be your doctor,

302
00:31:01,560 --> 00:31:03,040
I promise you.

303
00:31:04,326 --> 00:31:07,206
I will do everything in my power
to help you get better.

304
00:31:08,280 --> 00:31:10,120
Please, trust me.

305
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:21,520
Yes, P'Doc.

306
00:31:41,160 --> 00:31:44,000
If therapy is like riding a bike,

307
00:31:46,640 --> 00:31:49,280
are you ready to ride along with me?

308
00:31:58,760 --> 00:31:59,760
Yes.

309
00:33:14,920 --> 00:33:16,680
Let's do this together.

310
00:33:23,680 --> 00:33:24,680
Yes.

311
00:34:28,200 --> 00:34:31,280
- Beautiful, isn't it?
- Yeah.

312
00:34:35,360 --> 00:34:36,800
The view or the person?

313
00:34:38,200 --> 00:34:39,320
The person.

314
00:34:40,960 --> 00:34:43,760
I brought you some water.

315
00:34:48,600 --> 00:34:50,480
Are you this kind to everyone?

316
00:34:51,000 --> 00:34:53,160
Nope. Just you.

317
00:34:57,440 --> 00:34:58,679
What's your name?

318
00:34:58,680 --> 00:34:59,760
I'm Soda.

319
00:35:00,040 --> 00:35:01,760
- And you?
- Lemon.

320
00:35:02,200 --> 00:35:04,400
We're a good match. Lemon and Soda.

321
00:35:04,720 --> 00:35:06,840
- Are you imagining things?
- No.

322
00:35:07,080 --> 00:35:09,960
Haven't you ever had
a “Lemon Soda” drink?

323
00:35:10,360 --> 00:35:11,720
And do you like it?

324
00:35:13,240 --> 00:35:14,360
I love it.

325
00:35:14,840 --> 00:35:16,120
Don't you?

326
00:35:17,160 --> 00:35:18,280
I do.

327
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:22,239
Aren't you going to have some water?

328
00:35:22,240 --> 00:35:23,800
I already did.

329
00:35:31,160 --> 00:35:32,360
Drink it?

330
00:35:52,280 --> 00:35:53,480
Nava…

331
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:55,600
look at you.

332
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:58,120
Can you get up? Come on.

333
00:36:02,360 --> 00:36:04,040
Oh, my.

334
00:36:04,760 --> 00:36:05,760
Look,

335
00:36:07,320 --> 00:36:08,600
you're covered in sand.

336
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:11,279
Are you really okay?

337
00:36:11,280 --> 00:36:13,040
I'm fine. Gotta sit down.

338
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:21,640
Thanks.

339
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:31,720
I didn't think... I'd make it this far.

340
00:36:33,040 --> 00:36:35,360
Why? Are you exhausted?

341
00:36:36,400 --> 00:36:38,200
Yes, I am.

342
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:39,720
But...

343
00:36:41,280 --> 00:36:42,320
it feels good.

344
00:36:58,000 --> 00:36:59,960
First time seeing this side of you.

345
00:37:02,640 --> 00:37:03,720
Which side?

346
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:07,000
You know... the side that isn't a host.

347
00:37:07,440 --> 00:37:09,760
The athlete side. The cyclist side.

348
00:37:13,480 --> 00:37:14,480
And...

349
00:37:15,040 --> 00:37:16,200
is it a good side?

350
00:37:18,640 --> 00:37:20,840
Yeah... it's good.

351
00:37:25,320 --> 00:37:26,720
Do you like it?

352
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:31,040
I do.

353
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:37,080
Like it how?

354
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:42,040
As a friend.

355
00:37:44,600 --> 00:37:45,640
Then...

356
00:37:46,086 --> 00:37:48,406
let's keep riding together like this.

357
00:37:51,640 --> 00:37:52,640
Mm.

358
00:37:53,200 --> 00:37:54,840
For as long as I can handle it.

359
00:38:00,200 --> 00:38:01,520
Let's go.

360
00:38:05,440 --> 00:38:06,440
Careful there.

361
00:38:11,760 --> 00:38:14,000
Alright, everyone! It's time!

362
00:38:14,040 --> 00:38:16,040
Now, it's time to head back!

363
00:38:16,080 --> 00:38:17,999
And remember, this is very important!

364
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:21,320
Check your safety gear
and make sure everything is ready!

365
00:38:21,640 --> 00:38:23,280
Alright! Let's go!

366
00:38:32,160 --> 00:38:33,400
Whoa! Hey!

367
00:38:35,040 --> 00:38:36,640
Are you okay?

368
00:38:38,760 --> 00:38:39,760
You alright?

369
00:38:41,440 --> 00:38:42,640
Let me go!

370
00:38:42,680 --> 00:38:44,079
Whoa, calm down!

371
00:38:44,080 --> 00:38:45,080
Go away!

372
00:38:45,920 --> 00:38:47,679
What's wrong? I'm just trying to help.

373
00:38:47,680 --> 00:38:51,280
- Don't touch me!
- Relax, I'm just helping.

374
00:38:51,400 --> 00:38:52,960
Get away from me!

375
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:54,599
- Hey, take it...
- I said don't touch me!!

376
00:38:54,600 --> 00:38:57,680
Tawan, move back!

377
00:39:04,120 --> 00:39:05,400
Sailom.

378
00:39:05,680 --> 00:39:06,880
Sailom.

379
00:39:11,520 --> 00:39:13,080
I'm right here.

380
00:39:15,480 --> 00:39:17,320
Can you hear me?

381
00:39:20,720 --> 00:39:22,960
I understand you, Sailom.

382
00:39:28,120 --> 00:39:30,400
Take a deep breath. Slowly...

383
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:39,720
Look into my eyes, okay?

384
00:39:42,200 --> 00:39:43,920
Look at me.

385
00:39:59,000 --> 00:40:00,640
Breathe in...

386
00:40:03,440 --> 00:40:05,320
and breathe out slowly.

387
00:40:21,360 --> 00:40:22,520
I'm sorry.

388
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:25,800
I'm… so sorry, P'Doc.

389
00:40:27,760 --> 00:40:29,880
You don't have to apologize.

390
00:40:30,320 --> 00:40:32,160
You did nothing wrong.

391
00:40:37,600 --> 00:40:39,640
I'm right here with you.

392
00:40:54,240 --> 00:40:55,840
Hey, Sailom.

393
00:40:56,080 --> 00:40:58,880
Are you still stressing about
what happened at the bike trip?

394
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:00,759
Of course I am.

395
00:41:00,760 --> 00:41:03,280
I totally ruined his trip.

396
00:41:03,720 --> 00:41:05,999
Ruined it how? Everything went fine.

397
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:07,640
Everyone made it back home safely.

398
00:41:07,680 --> 00:41:09,040
Nobody got hurt.

399
00:41:09,720 --> 00:41:12,080
But they were all shocked because of me.

400
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:14,200
If it wasn't for my condition,

401
00:41:15,440 --> 00:41:17,720
P'Doc's trip
wouldn't have been so disrupted.

402
00:41:18,920 --> 00:41:20,840
You're overthinking it.

403
00:41:20,880 --> 00:41:22,920
P'Doc didn't even say a word about it.

404
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:25,360
Or maybe he did,
but we didn't know?

405
00:41:25,440 --> 00:41:28,600
If your mouth is so free,
just stuff it with this!

406
00:41:29,400 --> 00:41:30,520
Damn you!

407
00:41:33,240 --> 00:41:35,880
Ugh! What am I going to do?!

408
00:41:38,840 --> 00:41:41,040
- Thank you for coming.
- Yes.

409
00:41:41,080 --> 00:41:42,240
Thank you.

410
00:41:45,200 --> 00:41:46,720
What can I get for you?

411
00:41:46,800 --> 00:41:49,520
A cheesecake and a Thai tea, please.

412
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:51,880
A cheesecake and a Thai tea… and?

413
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:54,199
- A pink milk, please.
- Got it.

414
00:41:54,224 --> 00:41:55,944
Wow, we're really busy today.

415
00:41:56,840 --> 00:41:59,840
It's been non-stop
since the bike trip ended.

416
00:42:00,280 --> 00:42:02,640
Oh, please help make some more desserts.

417
00:42:02,680 --> 00:42:05,480
Sure thing. As soon as I
finish making this cup.

418
00:42:05,600 --> 00:42:07,000
- Thank you.
- Of course.

419
00:42:10,680 --> 00:42:14,000
Does the chain come off
when you're picking up speed?

420
00:42:15,760 --> 00:42:19,439
I think it's an issue with the gears.
Please have a seat and wait.

421
00:42:19,440 --> 00:42:20,520
Thank you.

422
00:42:24,720 --> 00:42:26,359
You can wait over here.

423
00:42:26,360 --> 00:42:28,439
Or if you'd like some coffee,

424
00:42:28,440 --> 00:42:29,840
we have a café over there.

425
00:42:29,880 --> 00:42:32,040
I think I'll wait at the café.

426
00:42:32,080 --> 00:42:33,600
Certainly. Right this way.

427
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:47,080
How long will you stand there?

428
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:48,800
Help me fix these.

429
00:42:52,040 --> 00:42:54,679
Stop posing already. Hurry up.

430
00:42:54,680 --> 00:42:55,720
Fine.

431
00:42:56,080 --> 00:42:57,560
Help me take this wheel off.

432
00:42:59,320 --> 00:43:00,560
Hey, Tawan!

433
00:43:01,400 --> 00:43:03,640
Can you edit a clip for our page?

434
00:43:03,960 --> 00:43:06,200
Look at all these bikes around you.

435
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:12,880
Ever since your bike trip ended,

436
00:43:13,640 --> 00:43:16,040
the shop's been flooded!

437
00:43:18,480 --> 00:43:20,319
Forget about editing clips.

438
00:43:20,320 --> 00:43:22,400
I don't even have time to breathe.

439
00:43:25,160 --> 00:43:26,040
By the way,

440
00:43:26,041 --> 00:43:27,680
how's that kid doing?

441
00:43:28,040 --> 00:43:29,040
Which kid?

442
00:43:29,760 --> 00:43:31,400
The kid who freaked out.

443
00:43:33,486 --> 00:43:35,246
Oh, you mean Sailom?

444
00:43:36,840 --> 00:43:38,759
You saw it yourself.

445
00:43:38,760 --> 00:43:40,280
He can't be touched.

446
00:43:40,560 --> 00:43:44,760
Is this the patient
you told me and Sky about that time?

447
00:43:45,480 --> 00:43:46,480
Yep.

448
00:43:47,800 --> 00:43:48,920
That's a tough one.

449
00:43:49,520 --> 00:43:50,720
Good luck with that.

450
00:44:02,800 --> 00:44:04,440
How many more bikes are left?

451
00:44:06,680 --> 00:44:12,200
Give it a try in the next couple of
days. It should be working fine now.

452
00:44:12,473 --> 00:44:15,233
I just had the mechanic
double-check and test everything.

453
00:44:16,480 --> 00:44:17,880
Thank you so much.

454
00:44:17,920 --> 00:44:22,360
If you run into any more issues,
just let us know. We're happy to help.

455
00:44:22,480 --> 00:44:23,920
Yes, thank you.

456
00:44:23,960 --> 00:44:25,040
You're welcome.

457
00:44:29,320 --> 00:44:30,320
Sailom?

458
00:44:43,080 --> 00:44:44,960
You're here to see me, right?

459
00:44:50,960 --> 00:44:53,480
If there's anything you want to say,

460
00:44:53,560 --> 00:44:54,840
I'm listening.

461
00:44:58,320 --> 00:45:01,600
I'm so sorry for ruining your trip.

462
00:45:03,240 --> 00:45:05,200
I really didn't mean it.

463
00:45:05,240 --> 00:45:07,000
Please don't be mad at me.

464
00:45:08,480 --> 00:45:11,200
If there's anything I can do to help,

465
00:45:11,600 --> 00:45:13,000
please tell me.

466
00:45:13,720 --> 00:45:16,040
I don't want to feel guilty anymore.

467
00:45:18,200 --> 00:45:20,520
You didn't do anything wrong.

468
00:45:22,920 --> 00:45:25,000
If you're worried that I'm angry,

469
00:45:25,560 --> 00:45:28,560
don't be. I'm not mad at all.

470
00:45:29,560 --> 00:45:31,000
I actually understand.

471
00:45:33,720 --> 00:45:34,840
Really?

472
00:45:36,240 --> 00:45:37,320
Really.

473
00:45:42,400 --> 00:45:45,440
I actually am looking for some help.

474
00:45:46,760 --> 00:45:48,120
Know how to edit videos?

475
00:45:49,040 --> 00:45:51,320
- Edit videos?
- Yes.

476
00:45:52,240 --> 00:45:55,200
I need someone to edit
the bike trip clips for our page.

477
00:45:55,920 --> 00:45:57,160
Can you do that?

478
00:45:58,880 --> 00:46:00,760
Yes! I can do that!

479
00:46:07,400 --> 00:46:08,400
Hurry up!

480
00:46:08,480 --> 00:46:09,960
Yeah, I'm on it.

481
00:46:10,920 --> 00:46:13,040
Wait! Keep this part.

482
00:46:13,080 --> 00:46:14,280
This shot is beautiful.

483
00:46:14,640 --> 00:46:15,960
Put this clip right here!

484
00:46:16,000 --> 00:46:17,000
Geez.

485
00:46:17,480 --> 00:46:19,640
Why don't you do it yourself?

486
00:46:21,120 --> 00:46:23,080
Here's the mouse.

487
00:46:27,160 --> 00:46:28,360
Please, continue.

488
00:46:29,560 --> 00:46:32,360
I promise I'll be quiet.

489
00:46:32,400 --> 00:46:34,400
Not a peep from me.

490
00:46:34,680 --> 00:46:36,920
If you can't even edit,
why did you volunteer?

491
00:46:38,320 --> 00:46:41,320
P'Doc couldn't find anyone to help.

492
00:46:41,680 --> 00:46:45,079
I must do anything
I can do to help him. Right?

493
00:46:45,080 --> 00:46:46,880
Want to help your boyfriend, huh?

494
00:46:47,120 --> 00:46:48,280
Come on!

495
00:46:48,440 --> 00:46:50,720
We're just doctor and patient!

496
00:46:51,240 --> 00:46:52,840
We're not dating.

497
00:46:53,520 --> 00:46:54,880
Really?

498
00:46:56,080 --> 00:46:59,280
But the doctor's necklace
is around the patient's neck.

499
00:47:08,280 --> 00:47:10,320
You better buy me beers after this.

500
00:47:11,240 --> 00:47:14,279
Fine. I'll buy you a whole factory.

501
00:47:14,280 --> 00:47:16,160
Perfect. Now, I'm motivated.

502
00:47:17,320 --> 00:47:18,840
Keep the orders coming.

503
00:47:21,200 --> 00:47:23,720
Oh, this music isn't quite right.

504
00:47:24,120 --> 00:47:26,320
- This one is better.
- Copy that.

505
00:47:40,640 --> 00:47:42,440
Time really flies, doesn't it?

506
00:47:42,920 --> 00:47:47,280
It feels like just yesterday
we were all having dinner together.

507
00:47:47,600 --> 00:47:48,920
It really does, Mom.

508
00:47:50,040 --> 00:47:53,280
Remember what your dad told you?

509
00:47:53,760 --> 00:47:55,680
No matter what happens,

510
00:47:55,960 --> 00:47:57,800
love one another.

511
00:47:58,080 --> 00:47:59,560
Because family

512
00:47:59,600 --> 00:48:01,280
is the most important thing.

513
00:48:02,560 --> 00:48:03,640
We remember, Mom.

514
00:48:04,320 --> 00:48:06,400
But we still fight all the time.

515
00:48:07,520 --> 00:48:08,920
It happens.

516
00:48:09,320 --> 00:48:10,600
I know.

517
00:48:10,760 --> 00:48:13,440
You can fight, but once it's over,

518
00:48:13,480 --> 00:48:15,320
always forgive each other.

519
00:48:16,200 --> 00:48:18,080
I miss Dad.

520
00:48:19,680 --> 00:48:21,800
I miss him too.

521
00:48:25,240 --> 00:48:27,080
So, what's for dinner tonight?

522
00:48:29,080 --> 00:48:30,880
A seafood BBQ by the beach?

523
00:48:31,640 --> 00:48:34,400
Can… I invite my friends over?

524
00:48:36,400 --> 00:48:38,080
If you do, I'm inviting mine too.

525
00:48:38,360 --> 00:48:41,600
Good. I'll invite the kids
from the shop to join us.

526
00:49:18,520 --> 00:49:20,120
Who do you live here with?

527
00:49:27,560 --> 00:49:28,560
Well...

528
00:49:30,280 --> 00:49:33,680
my parents split up when I was a kid.

529
00:49:35,520 --> 00:49:37,800
And back then,
I chose to stay with my mom.

530
00:49:38,800 --> 00:49:41,000
Maybe my dad is still mad at me

531
00:49:41,520 --> 00:49:43,320
because I didn't choose him.

532
00:49:45,040 --> 00:49:46,439
The truth is...

533
00:49:46,440 --> 00:49:48,520
I never wanted to choose at all.

534
00:49:51,400 --> 00:49:53,360
Because no matter who I chose...

535
00:49:54,680 --> 00:49:56,840
I would still be the one at fault.

536
00:50:11,280 --> 00:50:12,720
(Next Episode)
Never had a boyfriend.

537
00:50:12,840 --> 00:50:14,480
Then... give me a kiss.

538
00:50:15,400 --> 00:50:18,960
A host and a customer.
Is it really possible?

539
00:50:19,840 --> 00:50:22,800
Take this home, so your
grandma can have a warm meal.

540
00:50:23,720 --> 00:50:26,000
Grandma?! Grandma!

541
00:50:26,360 --> 00:50:28,480
Your grandma is going to be okay.

542
00:50:30,040 --> 00:50:31,880
I want to see Nabnueng.

543
00:50:33,360 --> 00:50:35,200
It's been a long time, son.

544
00:50:38,440 --> 00:50:39,440
NO!

545
00:50:39,520 --> 00:50:40,520
Sailom!

